    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> This doesn't seem to regress anything, but I am also not sure what it really fixes.\n\nThe only noticable case in the shipping mods is the idle animation (that flag thing) of the RA airfield, which stopped after its active animation ran once.\nWe don't have a `WithIdleAnimation` trait, the sprite body itself loops its `Sequence`. Some traits like `WithActiveAnimation` cancelled that looping, but did not restart it after finishing, getting stuck at the last active frame instead. This means that before this fix, idle animations on tesla coils/obelisks, helipads, service depots, nuke silos etc. would get broken as soon as their special action was triggered and never recover.\n\nThis fixes it by always triggering the sprite bodies' default animation after the custom active animation has finished (see `CancelCustomAnimation` in `WithSpriteBody` for reference).\nBasically, this applies the same fix we already implemented earlier on some other traits like `WithBuildingPlacedAnimation` and `WithAttackAnimation`.\n"
  },
